Business Brief -- Revere Fund Inc.:
   Shareholders Clear Merger
   With Nature Food Centres
When the merger is completed, Mr. Rossetti will own 49.9%
of the then-outstanding Revere common shares and, as
previously reported, will become president and chief
executive of Revere.
   Michael E. Chaney, Revere's president, will become vice
president and will manage the existing portfolio of the
surviving company. James F. Leary will remain chairman of
Revere, the company said.